  "sourceNotes": [
    {
      "brand": "Subway",
      "sourceFile": "Subway_AU_Best_Value.xlsx",
      "notes": [
        "Notes & Method",
        "COUNTRY: Australia, to match the GYG and McDonald's sheets. Say if you want another country.",
        "NUTRITION (solid): Serve size (g), energy (kJ) and protein (g) are from Subway's official Australia Nutrition Summary.",
        "Values are for the standard 6-inch sub (white bread + standard salads, no extra cheese/sauce unless the sub includes it).",
        "Footlong rows use 2x the 6-inch values, per Subway's own note ('Double values for approximate Footlong nutrition').",
        "Energy (Cal) = kJ / 4.184. Adding cheese, sauces, avo or extra protein increases weight and energy beyond these figures.",
        "PRICES (caveat): Subway is franchised and prices vary noticeably by store. The 6-inch prices here are representative AU",
        "menu prices c. 2026; FOOTLONG prices are estimated at ~1.55x the 6-inch (real footlongs are often 1.5-1.7x). Verify in-store/app.",
        "The best real-world value is the promo pricing: the ~$7 Six-Inch Value Range and the ~$8 Footlong Sub of the Day.",
        "METRICS:",
        "Grams / $  = serve size (g) / price  ->  the literal 'most food per dollar' measure (headline, green column).",
        "kJ / $     = energy (kJ) / price; Protein g / $ = protein (g) / price.",
        "KEY TAKEAWAYS:",
        "Footlongs beat 6-inch on every per-dollar metric: 2x the food for only ~1.5x the price. If maximising food/$, go footlong.",
        "Deal-priced subs win outright - an $8 Sub of the Day footlong is ~430g+ for $8 (~54 g/$).",
        "For protein per dollar, the meatier footlongs (Chicken & Bacon Ranch, Steak, Chicken Teriyaki/Schnitzel) lead.",
        "Cookies look efficient on grams/$ and kJ/$ but are sugar, not a meal.",
        "All value columns are live Excel formulas - edit any price or serve size and the rankings update."
      ]
    },
    {
      "brand": "GYG",
      "sourceFile": "GYG_Best_Value.xlsx",
      "notes": [
        "Notes & Method",
        "PRICES: Taken from the attached GYG national menu (the ‘from’ / base price for each item).",
        "GYG prices vary by location, ordering channel (in-store vs delivery apps) and over time, so treat these as a guide.",
        "NUTRITION: From the GYG Allergen, Ingredient & Nutritional guide, ‘current at June 25, 2024’.",
        "Serve size (g), energy (kJ) and protein (g) are taken directly from that guide.",
        "Energy (Cal) is calculated as kJ / 4.184.",
        "FILLING: To compare like-for-like, the standard filling is Grilled Chicken where a choice exists.",
        "Exceptions: Quesadilla = cheese only (its base price); $3 Taco = ground beef (only option);",
        "Tender items = crispy chicken tender; corn-chip/queso/fries sides use the dip/seasoning noted.",
        "Brisket adds ~$1 and other fillings shift weight/energy slightly, so value rankings move a little by filling.",
        "METRICS:",
